6:
I-It shouldn't be a problem, but just
in case! Is it truly all right if I break
this device?
8:
I am not proud to say this, but
neither the kingdom of Mirea nor its
princess can afford to pay for it!
11:
Don't worry. I have a spare on hand
in the event that this one breaks. We
can proceed without worry.
14:
...If you're this healthy to begin with,
the necessity of this seems
doubtful...
22:
We were supposed to be getting
examined for any aftereffects we
might have picked up during the
Magia Fest, but...
25:
Is this really just a checkup? Don't
you think putting her in a machine
like that might cause a problem
with Mirea?
30:
If you're worried about sparking
international problems, you crossed
the line by getting his help in the first
place.
35:
Life Force Manipulation—the art of
controlling the very flow of life itself.
With it, even achieving
quasi-immortality isn't out of the
question.
37:
In other words, Toria should be
essentially shriveled up by now.
43:
She looks pretty lively to me,
though?!
47:
N-no, it's just... This is more of a
humanitarian issue, or something...
58:
These are her wishes, and she was
prepared for this. Given the
circumstances, this was the logical
course of action.
61:
...Though I never expected there to
be so much power to be extracted
in the first place. Put another way,
Mirea's princess is built different.
63:
I'm very curious about this. May I
check to see whether reproducibility
is possible?
68:
I don't really know what that means,
but that's probably fine!
73:
U-um, wait! That doesn't sound find
at all!
79:
Sorry to keep you waiting. You're up
next.
91:
N-no, not really, I was just focused
on something...
98:
I'll take the necessary info from here.
You can stay put.
100:
I'd also like you to tell me your story
so that I can decipher that
information.
104:
...You want me to tell you about
when I had that spell cast on me?
110:
What I mean is... May I ask you why
you choose to make music?
114:
Oh, that? It's not an uncommon
thing for people to do... There's
nothing special about me there...
118:
I just slog along doing whatever until
something's more or less finished...
122: ...Bear in mind, this is only a theory.
125:
I once thought of singing as a way
of seeking the truth.
128:
That is, both universal truth and the
truth you carry within you. We define
outlines and draw them out, refining
technique and form.
130:
This is merely my own impression,
but I see you and I as kindred spirits
of sorts.
137:
Or, I mean... It would be cool if I could
really make music like that.
140:
I just want to reach... somebody with
my music. I think that's all there is to
it.
144:
Is that so? Do you suppose that your
music might give you insight into
what others are feeling, too?
147:
If you put it into words like that, it
probably sounds a little crazy.
151:
Hmm. This is a difficult issue to
address.
155:
I-I don't really know what I'm talking
about! So...
159:
When I heard your song, I felt as
though I was meeting someone
from my past.
162:
Perhaps you could say that what I
received from you cannot be easily
put into words.
168:
I'm just speculating, and there's
nothing rational about what I'm
saying. Don't worry about it.
171:
Treasure your world in the way you
see it. Listening to my speculations
too much may even have a
negative impact on you.
173:
Hmm. I wonder whether I, too, desire
to express that which cannot be
expressed through words.
176: ...I suppose you haven't given up yet.
178:
And for that, you are worthy of
respect. You're stronger than I was.
181:
You will surely arrive at a different
place than I did, and you will save
others where I could not.
184: And that is a wonderful thing.
192:
That was my intention from the
beginning, yes...
198:
Maybe a little. But it's kind of like a
song, in a way... Sometimes it's
better to be less than direct.
205:
Yes.
It wasn't too... roundabout, was it?
218:
I-it's okay! It's not capable of going
on a rampage or anything!
226:
I wonder if that ghost I included as
part of the test is responsible?
232:
When'd you do that? Why does stuff
like this happen every time?!
236:
I'll handle things from here in my
own way.
238: Will you do the same, Hibiki?
